      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(web): allow closing direct messages",
        "body": "Closes #30.\n\n## Shape\n\nThis implements \"close DM\" as a per-user hide/restore state, not destructive deletion.\n\nThe shape is intentionally narrow: closing removes a DM from the current user's list without deleting history or membership, while reopening the same one-to-one DM reuses the existing conversation rather than creating another copy. I kept this focused because maintainers are more likely to appreciate a small DM-list lifecycle affordance than a broader notification/mute/privacy policy PR.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Added per-user hidden state for direct conversations in SQLite and Postgres.\n- `GET /api/dms` now omits DMs hidden by the current user.\n- Added `GET /api/dms/{conversation_id}` so hidden authorized DMs still resolve from direct routes/links.\n- Added `DELETE /api/dms/{conversation_id}` to close a DM for the current human user.\n- Reopening the same one-to-one DM reuses the existing conversation and unhides it for the actor.\n- A new root DM message resurfaces the conversation for members, including open browser sessions via realtime handling.\n- Bot tokens are forbidden from closing/hiding human DM state.\n- Updated OpenAPI, TS SDK, generated SQL, embedded web assets, and focused tests.\n\n## Non-goals\n\n- No hard delete or message-history deletion.\n- No group-DM leave/rejoin semantics.\n- No mute, notification, search, or unread-policy changes.\n- No bot-routing behavior changes.\n\n## Proof\n\nProof package: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/proof.md\n\nVisual checkpoints:\n- Visible before close: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/01-dm-visible-before-close.png\n- Hidden after close: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/02-dm-hidden-after-close.png\n- Hidden route still opens: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/03-hidden-direct-route-opens.png\n- Reopen reuses and unhides: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/04-reopen-reuses-and-unhides.png\n- New root message resurfaces DM: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/05-new-message-resurfaces-dm.png\n- Resurfaced message opened: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/06-resurfaced-message-opened.png\n- Current head actions menu open: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/07-actions-menu-open.png\n- Current head Undo visible after close: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/08-undo-visible-after-close.png\n- Current head Undo restores same DM: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/09-undo-restores-same-dm.png\n\nLog/data proof includes:\n- conversation `dm_01kvazkm960f33k8z52b90m9rn`\n- reopened same conversation: `true`\n- resurface message `msg_01kvazkmmfb6vnnfw7nj4yw741`\n- event `evt_01kvazkmmfb6vnnfw7nmktx6hk`, type `message.created`, seq `1`\n- server request sequence covering `POST /api/dms`, `DELETE /api/dms/{id}`, direct hidden `GET /api/dms/{id}`, reopen `POST /api/dms`, and root-message resurface.\n- current-head menu/Undo proof: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/proof-current-head-menu-undo.json\n- current-head server log: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PollyBot13/clickclack/proof/clickclack-pr-30-dm-close/proof/pr-30-dm-close/server-current-head.log\n- current-head conversation `dm_01kvdqdq3wptn9j4c0vbkm5dqb`\n- current-head hidden direct `GET /api/dms/{id}` status: `200`\n- current-head Undo `POST /api/dms/{id}/open` status: `200`\n- current-head Undo restored same conversation: `true`\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm generate:sqlc`\n- `go test ./apps/api/internal/store/sqlite -run 'TestHideDirectConversation|TestCreateDirectConversation'`\n- `go test ./apps/api/internal/httpapi -run 'TestHTTP|TestBotToken'`\n- `go test ./apps/api/internal/httpapi ./apps/api/internal/store/sqlite`\n- `pnpm fmt:ts:check`\n- `pnpm --filter @clickclack/web typecheck && pnpm --filter @clickclack/sdk-ts typecheck && pnpm typecheck`\n- `pnpm exec playwright test tests/e2e/chat.spec.ts -g \"closes direct messages\"`\n- `pnpm check`\n- `git diff --cached --check`\n\n## Review loop\n\nCodex review was run with the corrected auth path on the staged/committed PR diff: `CODEX_HOME=$HOME/.codex codex review --base origin/main`.\n\nReview findings fixed before opening:\n- Avoided double unread bump when realtime resurface reloads the DM list from the server.\n- Ensured sending a root DM into a hidden conversation also unhides it for the sender, not only other members.\n\nFinal Codex review result: no discrete introduced issue found.\n\n\n## Potential follow-up\n\nThe current UI says “Close direct message” because this PR keeps the behavior narrow: the conversation is hidden from the current user’s DM list, but history, membership, direct links, and resurfacing all remain intact.\n\nIf maintainers like this direction, a follow-up PR could make this more explicitly archive-like: for example wording around “Hide” or “Archive”, plus an archived/closed DM recovery surface so users can browse and restore previously hidden conversations without needing a direct link, recreating the DM, or waiting for a new message.\n",
